%% Journey 1: Process Definition Deployment
%% Deploy a BPMN resource end-to-end through the system.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Dev as Developer / Modeler
    participant GW as Gateway (REST / gRPC)
    participant Auth as Auth Layer
    participant Broker as Broker
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant State as State Store (RocksDB)
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant RExp as RDBMS Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch / OpenSearch
    participant DB as RDBMS
    participant Operate as Operate
    participant Tasklist as Tasklist

    Dev->>GW: Deploy BPMN resource (REST POST /v2/deployments or gRPC DeployResource)
    GW->>Auth: Authenticate & authorize
    Auth-->>GW: ✅ Allowed
    GW->>Broker: BrokerDeployResourceRequest (routed to partition 1)
    Broker->>Engine: DEPLOYMENT:CREATE command
    Engine->>Engine: Parse & validate BPMN (bpmn-model)
    Engine->>State: Store ProcessDefinition
    Engine->>Log: Write DEPLOYMENT:CREATED event
    Engine->>Log: Write PROCESS:CREATED event
    Log->>CExp: Export DEPLOYMENT + PROCESS records
    CExp->>ES: Bulk index to process-definition index
    Log->>RExp: Export DEPLOYMENT + PROCESS records
    RExp->>DB: INSERT into process_definition table
    Note over Operate,Tasklist: Webapps query secondary storage (eventually consistent)
    Operate->>ES: Search process definitions
    Tasklist->>ES: Search startable processes
